cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.DS 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper proposes a novel algorithmic trading model using 2-D bar chart images and a deep Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) model. This directly involves computer vision techniques and image processing, making it highly likely to belong to this sub-category. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper utilizes a deep CNN model for the algorithmic trading model, which falls under the domain of machine learning. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes an AI-based approach for financial trading using deep learning techniques. 
4. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The paper involves the retrieval of information from stock bar chart images for financial trading purposes. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper involves the use of sliding windows of 30-day bar charts for generating 2-D images, which involves data structures and algorithms.
